## What it does

- Starts a browser preview with `:GoLiveMarkdownStart`
- Auto-updates on markdown edits and cursor movement (`*.md`)
- Syncs browser line clicks back to Neovim (Double click in browser)

## Install and configure

### lazy.nvim

```lua
{
  "pompos02/go-live-markdown.nvim",
  ft = "markdown",
  config = function()
    -- Optional: override host binary path.
    -- vim.g.go_live_markdown_host_prog = "/absolute/path/to/go-live-markdown-nvim"
  end,
}
```

By default, the plugin resolves the host binary in this order:
1. `vim.g.go_live_markdown_host_prog`
2. local `./bin/go-live-markdown-nvim` inside the plugin
3. `go-live-markdown-nvim` from your `$PATH`

## Binary and building

This repository ships with a **Linux binary bundled** at `bin/go-live-markdown-nvim`.

On **macOS** (and other non-Linux systems), build the host binary locally.
The plugin will then pick up `./bin/go-live-markdown-nvim` automatically.

### lazy.nvim (recommended for non linux systems)

```lua
{
  "pompos02/go-live-markdown.nvim",
  ft = "markdown",
  build = "./build",
}
```

Requirements:
- `go` must be installed and available in `$PATH`
- the plugin build step must run at least once

If you want to build it yourself:
```bash
./build
```

That script compiles `./cmd/go-live-markdown-nvim` into `./bin/go-live-markdown-nvim`.

## Quick test

Use `markdown-test.md` in this repository to quickly verify the plugin behavior:

1. Open `markdown-test.md` in Neovim
2. Run `:GoLiveMarkdownStart`
3. Edit text and move your cursor to confirm live updates
4. Double click a line in the browser preview to confirm sync back to Neovim



> [!NOTE]
> - A known bug is that only one browser tab is supported reliably at a time right now (the connection jumpts back and forth).
> - Only one Go host/preview server instance is supported at a time.
> - Almost all of the client side logic was written by AI
